content:
I use music to help me concentrate. I normally deep dive into a particular artist or genre. Today I discovered the Alan Lomax archive on youtube. He archived old hand me down songs mostly of southern black America. I'm glad he did or they'd probably be lost. These gems were probably heard by white European settlers and mixed with their folk instruments to form one of my favorite musical genres, bluegrass. Enjoy.

https://yt.artemislena.eu/channel/UCInpAOuv6nqdf6EheU4Wfjg

content:
* I am not a woman, but I support equal rights, and the right to choose.

* I am not LGBTQ+, but I believe love is love.

* I am not trans, but I believe trans rights, are human rights.

* I am not black, but I believe black lives do indeed matter.

I do not need to be any of these to have empathy, sympathy, and compassion for their rights and struggles in life. It is called being a human being and I wish more people would try it sometimes.
